Self-Types:
 The "Only for Friends" Guard
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sometimes you want to write a Trait that only works if it’s mixed into a specific type of class.
 This is called a Self-Type.
 It’s like saying:
 "I am a MetricCollector,
 but I only know how to work when I’m part of a WebService."
\end_layout

