\begin_layout Subsection*
Sealed Traits:
 The Closed Door
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A 
\series bold
Sealed Trait
\series default
 is a powerful safety feature.
 When you mark a trait as sealed,
 you are telling the compiler:
 "Every single class that implements this trait must be in this exact same file."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is the secret sauce for 
\series bold
Pattern Matching
\series default
.
 If the compiler knows every possible implementation of a trait,
 it can warn you if your match statement forgot one!
\end_layout

