\begin_layout Standard
The Pragmatic Import
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Scala’s import system is incredibly flexible,
 allowing you to clean up your code and avoid naming "collisions" (like having two different Date classes).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
The Wildcard:

\series default
\emph on
 import scala.util.control.*
\emph default
 imports everything in that package.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
The Rename:

\series default
\emph on
 import java.util.{Date => JDate}
\emph default
 lets you use JDate in your code to avoid confusion with other Date types.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
The Selective:

\series default
\emph on
 import sttp.client3.{basicRequest,
 UriContext}
\emph default
 only brings in exactly what you need.
\end_layout

